{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Legalise small scale Cannabis cultivation for medical patients",
        "additional_details": "I am writing to the members of Parliament in order to change the legislation surrounding Medical Cannabis.\r\n\r\nCurrently, patients with a Medical Cannabis (hereafter referred to as MC) prescription can only receive their medication through private clinics.\r\n\r\nMy proposal would be to allow patients, with a prescription, to cultivate and process Cannabis plants (C. sativa, indica, ruderalis) at home.\r\n\r\nThis medicine allows people to return to their normal lives, and prices can be prohibitively high.",
        "background": "Allow the cultivation of no more than three (3) Cannabis SP. plants for personal use if the patient has a Medical Cannabis prescription.",
